Hi all,

We are currently investigating a permission behavior observed in the UAT Power BI workspace.

Context:

* In DEV environment, the “Manage permissions” option is available on semantic models, allowing Build permissions to be assigned to users.
* In UAT environment, the same option is not available/visible, even though workspace roles have already been assigned.

Current observations:

* Workspace access is managed through BBS requests and corresponding MIM groups.
* Workspace roles (Admin, Member, Contributor, Viewer) appear to be centrally governed through enterprise access management.
* In UAT, semantic models and reports were published directly by me, but the “Manage permissions” option is still unavailable.

Hypothesis:
This may indicate that the UAT environment is governed by additional Power BI/Fabric restrictions preventing manual semantic model permission management, potentially requiring all access to be controlled exclusively through MIM groups and BBS processes.

Next validation step:
We will test whether another workspace admin/user can create and publish a report in the same UAT workspace and verify whether the “Manage permissions” option becomes available for that user.

Possible outcomes:

1. If another user can manage permissions:

   * there may be an additional hidden entitlement, ownership privilege, or governance role attached to the original workspace requester.

2. If another user also cannot manage permissions:

   * the limitation is likely environment/workspace governance related rather than user specific.

Potential resolution paths:

* Verify tenant/workspace governance settings with the Power BI/Fabric administration team
* Confirm whether semantic model sharing and Build permissions are intentionally restricted in UAT
* Evaluate whether Build access must instead be granted through MIM groups/BBS requests
* Verify whether App-based permission inheritance should be used instead of manual semantic model sharing

We will continue the investigation and share the outcome of the additional validation test.

